\pause

The expectation can be thought of as the \alert{center of mass}
if we place mass $p_X(x)$ at corresponding points $x$.

\vspace{0.1in} \pause

<<dragonwood_center_of_gravity, dependson='dragonwood_expectation', fig.height=2>>=
